**4. Transaction ID Propagation**
```java
public class TransactionContext {
    private static final ThreadLocal<String> txId = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public static void begin() { txId.set(UUID.randomUUID().toString()); }
    public static String getId() { return txId.get(); }
    public static void end() { txId.remove(); }
}
```

---

**Key rule:** always call `.remove()` in a `finally` block when using thread pools (Tomcat, Spring, etc.) to avoid leaking state across requests.
